olive oil
½ Onion
2 clove garlic
1 packet red lentils
20 g butter
1 sachet Mumbai Spice Blend
1 packet Bengal Curry Paste
1 packet tomato paste
2 cup water
½ tsp salt
1 packet Coconut Milk
1 Carrot
1 packet Green beans
pinch Chilli Flakes
6 Mini Flour Tortillas
1 packet Baby Leaves
½ packet Greek-Style Yoghurt
1 packet Coriander

• Finely chop onion (see ingredients) and garlic.
• Rinse red lentils.

• In a large deep frying pan, heat the butter and a
drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat. Cook
onion, stirring, until softened, 3-4 minutes.
• Add garlic and Mumbai spice blend and cook
until fragrant, 1 minute.
• Add a drizzle of olive oil, then add Bengal curry
paste and tomato paste and cook, stirring until
fragrant, 2 minutes.

• Add the water, salt, lentils and coconut milk to
the pan. Stir well to combine. Cover with a lid,
reduce the heat to medium and cook until the
lentils have softened, 20-25 minutes.
• While the lentils are cooking, grate carrot. Trim
and halve green beans.
• In the last 5 minutes of cook time, remove the
lid and stir through carrot and green beans.
Cook until softened.

TIP: Add a splash of water if the dhal looks dry.

• While the dhal is cooking, heat a medium frying
pan over medium-high heat with the olive oil
(21/2 tbs for 2 people / 1/3 cup for 4 people).
• Add a pinch of chilli flakes (if using) and cook
until fragrant, 1 minute.
• Transfer chilli-infused oil to a small bowl. Brush
(or spread using the back of a spoon) some chilli
oil over both sides of a mini flourtortilla.
• Return frying pan to medium-high heat, then
cook the tortilla until golden, 1 minute each
side. Transfer to a paper towel-lined plate.
• Repeat with remaining chilli oil and tortillas.

• When the dhal has finished cooking, stir through
baby leaves until wilted. Season with salt and
pepper.

TIP: Stir through some water with the baby leaves
if needed!

• Divide coconut lentil and green bean dhal
between bowls.
• Top with Greek-style yoghurt and tear over
coriander. Serve with chilli flatbreads. Enjoy!